# Item Effect Display Format

For items with **named effects** (effects that have both a name and a description):

## Required Layout

The effect box label (where "EFFECT" would go) **IS** the effect name:

```
-------------------------
[Effect name]              |
[description]              |
-------------------------
```

- **item-popup-effect-hint** = the effect name (e.g. "Infantry Grunt", "Firebreaker")
- **item-popup-effect-text** = the effect description

## Implementation

```html
<div class="item-popup-effect">
  <span class="item-popup-effect-hint">${escapeHtml(eff.name)}</span>
  <p class="item-popup-effect-text">${escapeHtml(eff.description)}</p>
</div>
```

## Do NOT

- Use generic labels like "Effect" or "Special Effect" when the effect has a name
- Put name and description on the same line with a colon
- Add a redundant name line â€” the hint IS the name

## Applies To

- Item special effects (from item-special-effects.ts: Infantry Grunt, Sturdy, Flame Ward, etc.)
- Weapon effects (Calibrated, Firebreaker, etc.)
- Any item effect with a `name` and `description` pair
